definition.value: One of the provinces of Cuba. The city of Havana is a separate province, surrounded by the province of Havana. La Habana Province has borders with the city of Havana, Pinar del Rio, and Matanzas.
One of the provinces of Cuba. The capital city of the province is also called Cienfuegos.

One of the provinces of Cuba, and was previously part of Camaguey Province. Its capital is Ciego de Avila, which lies on the Carretera Central (central highway), and the second city is Moron, further north.
One of the provinces of Cuba. Its capital is Sancti Spiritus.

One of the provinces of Cuba. It's located in the central region of the island bordering with the Atlantic at north, Matanzas Province by west, Sancti Spiritus by east, and Cienfuegos on the South. Villa Clara shares with Cienfuegos and Sancti Spiritus on the south the Escambray Mountain Range.

One of the provinces of Cuba. Major towns include Puerto Padre and Amancio, as well as the capital, Victoria de Las Tunas. The Las Tunas province was established in 1976, when it was split from the 'Oriente region.
One of the provinces of Cuba. Its capital is Bayamo.
A province of the Dominican Republic. Before 1952 it included what is now Independencia Province.
A province of the Dominican Republic. Until 1958 it included what is now Pedernales Province.
A province of the Dominican Republic.

A province of the Dominican Republic. Before 1992 it included what is now Hato Mayor province. Limita al este con la provincia de La Altagracia, al sur con las provincias La Altagracia y San Pedro de Macoris, y al oeste con la provincia Hato Mayor. Esta bordeada por el norte por el Oceano Atlantico. La capital provincial es la ciudad de Santa Cruz del Seibo.

One of the 31 provinces of the Dominican Republic. It is located in the western part of the country, on the border with Haiti. Its capital city is Comendador. It was a municipio of the San Juan province before being elevated to the category of province.
A province of the Dominican Republic. The province was split from El Seibo in 1992.
A province of the Dominican Republic.
A province of the Dominican Republic. Until 1992 it included what is now Monsenor Nouel province.
A province of the Dominican Republic. Originally known as Trinidad Sanchez Nagua, the name of its capital city, it was split from Samana in 1963.
A province of the Dominican Republic. The capital is also named La Romana. The province was split from La Altagracia in 1968, and includes both Isla Saona and Isla Catalina.
The easternmost province of the Dominican Republic. Punta Cana is located on the eastern shores of this province. Until 1968 it included what is now La Romana Province.
A province of the Dominican Republic. It was split from La Vega in 1992.
A province of the Dominican Republic on the border with Haiti. It was split from Baoruco in 1952.
The southernmost province of the Dominican Republic, including the offshore Isla Beata. It was split from Barahona in 1958.

A province of the Dominican Republic. Its capital is Santa Barbara de Samana, also known as Samana City. Samana is located on the coast of the Atlantic Ocean in the northeastern part of the Dominican Republic.
A province of the Dominican Republic, also the name of its capital city.
A province of the Dominican Republic. It was split from Espaillat Province in 1952.
A province in the southern Dominican Republic, west of the capital Santo Domingo. It included what is now Monte Plata Province until 1992. The provincial capital is San Cristobal.
A province of the Dominican Republic. Before 2002-01-01 it included what is now San Jose de Ocoa province.
One of the northern provinces of the Dominican Republic.
A province of the Dominican Republic. It was split from Duarte in 1952.
A province of the Dominican Republic, and also the name of its capital city. It was split from San Cristobal in 1992.
A province of the Dominican Republic. It was split from Monte Cristi in 1948.
A province of the Dominican Republic. It was split from the Distrito Nacional on 2004-10-01 16, 2001.
A province of the Dominican Republic.
A province of the Dominican Republic.
A province of the Dominican Republic. It was split from Santiago in 1959.
A province of the Dominican Republic, and also the name of the province's capital city. It was split from Peravia on 2002-01-01.
A department of El Salvador, located in the northwest of the country. The capital is the city of Chalatenango.
